02:30.264 --> 02:31.798
<i>Ladies and gentlemen...</i>

02:31.832 --> 02:34.100
<i>...please welcome 1972</i>

02:34.134 --> 02:36.804
<i>U.S. Open Women's
Singles Champion...</i>

02:36.836 --> 02:39.304
<i>...Billie Jean King.</i>

03:06.361 --> 03:08.531
Have you seen this?

03:08.564 --> 03:09.965
No. Hey, Gladys.

03:09.998 --> 03:11.098
You want a dance?

03:11.133 --> 03:12.366
I want a gun.

03:12.400 --> 03:13.533
They just snuck this out

03:13.568 --> 03:15.703
in the middle of the night.
Lowlifes.

03:15.737 --> 03:16.903
This is outrageous.

03:16.937 --> 03:19.506
And it's got Jack Kramer's
fingerprints all over it.

03:19.539 --> 03:22.074
You're absolutely
right it does.

03:22.110 --> 03:23.710
I know where he's hiding.

03:24.979 --> 03:26.479
You want to come?

03:26.513 --> 03:29.548
No. No, you go
do your thing.

03:29.582 --> 03:30.849
But good luck.

03:35.121 --> 03:37.221
Thank you very much, honey.

03:35.121 --> 03:37.221
Sure, Mr. Kramer.

03:37.254 --> 03:39.389
Thank you.

03:37.254 --> 03:39.389
Of course.

03:39.424 --> 03:40.825
They won't get
away with it.

03:40.858 --> 03:41.891
Uh-oh.

03:41.925 --> 03:43.593
You can't go in there.

03:43.627 --> 03:45.127
Excuse me.

03:45.163 --> 03:46.730
Wait a minute.

03:46.764 --> 03:48.765
Surprised in their lair.

03:48.798 --> 03:51.800
This is an unexpected
pleasure.

03:51.835 --> 03:54.871
My goodness, you both look
sensational, if I may say.

03:54.903 --> 03:55.836
You may not.

03:55.872 --> 03:57.372
You're not supposed
to be in here, you know.

03:57.406 --> 03:59.807
Because I'm a woman
or because I'm a Jew, Bob?

03:59.842 --> 04:02.678
Please, you're welcome here.
Have a seat.

04:04.445 --> 04:06.545
What can we do for you?

04:06.580 --> 04:08.281
Would you like
a glass of something maybe?

04:08.317 --> 04:09.784
No, thank you, Jack.

04:11.117 --> 04:13.151
I find it's best
to be clear before

04:13.187 --> 04:14.820
committing cold-blooded
murder, so...

04:15.323 --> 04:16.923
...clarify...

04:18.423 --> 04:19.690
...the press release.

04:19.725 --> 04:20.692
Ah, yes.

04:20.726 --> 04:22.293
It says here
that you're offering

04:22.327 --> 04:24.028
the men's winner $12,000...

04:24.062 --> 04:26.797
...and $1,500 to the women's.

04:26.831 --> 04:28.331
Those are the terms.

04:28.367 --> 04:30.033
The men's prize
needs to be that high

04:30.067 --> 04:31.300
to attract the best players.

04:31.334 --> 04:32.435
We're trying to make this

04:32.468 --> 04:34.170
the most prestigious
tournament in America.

04:34.204 --> 04:36.072
And paying the women
less than ever

04:36.107 --> 04:38.408
makes it more prestigious.
Uh...

04:38.440 --> 04:41.442
Well, it's simply a question
of what we can afford.

04:41.478 --> 04:43.345
People pay to see
the men play.

04:43.379 --> 04:44.713
They're the draw.

04:44.747 --> 04:46.949
They're eight times
more of a draw?

04:47.548 --> 04:48.581
Sorry?

04:48.617 --> 04:49.917
You're offering
the men's winner

04:49.951 --> 04:51.586
eight times that of the women.

04:51.620 --> 04:53.187
Do we bring in
an eighth of the crowd?

04:53.221 --> 04:55.288
I don't know
percentages, but...

04:55.322 --> 04:56.857
They sold the exact
same amount of tickets

04:56.891 --> 04:59.326
to the women's final today
as the men's.

04:59.360 --> 05:02.329
Isn't that right, Jack?

04:59.360 --> 05:02.329
Today, yeah, I suppose so.

05:02.362 --> 05:05.197
Same sales, same prize money.
Makes sense to me.

05:05.232 --> 05:06.866
Oh, come on.
Be reasonable.

05:06.899 --> 05:09.500
There's no way
that we could afford that.

05:09.535 --> 05:11.336
What's your argument, Jack?

05:12.872 --> 05:13.871
For one thing,

05:13.906 --> 05:16.441
the men have families
that they have to support.

05:16.475 --> 05:19.310
I'm the main breadwinner
in my family.

05:19.343 --> 05:21.211
Yeah. Yeah.

05:21.245 --> 05:22.445
Look.

05:25.615 --> 05:28.985
The men are simply...
more exciting to watch.

05:29.851 --> 05:31.185
They are.

05:31.220 --> 05:32.921
They're faster.

05:31.220 --> 05:32.921
Fact.

05:32.954 --> 05:34.222
And stronger.

05:32.954 --> 05:34.222
Fact.

05:34.257 --> 05:35.656
And more competitive.

05:35.690 --> 05:36.625
Just a fact.

05:36.658 --> 05:40.628
It's not your fault,
it's just... biology.

05:40.661 --> 05:44.464
That's not my point. We sell
the same amount of tickets.

05:45.665 --> 05:48.999
I'm sorry.
It's not going to happen.

05:51.670 --> 05:53.738
Well, if that's
the way it is...

05:55.408 --> 05:57.043
...we'll boycott
the tournament.

05:57.576 --> 05:58.576
Fact.

06:00.379 --> 06:02.612
Well, now...

06:02.648 --> 06:05.983
...we'll sure miss your pretty faces,
but go right ahead.

06:06.016 --> 06:07.382
Not only will we boycott,

06:07.418 --> 06:09.119
we'll set up
our own tournament.

06:09.153 --> 06:10.353
Fact.

06:10.387 --> 06:13.121
At the exact same time
as the Pacific Southwest.

06:13.156 --> 06:14.790
Fact.

06:14.824 --> 06:18.360
Be sure and send me tickets.
You have a good night, ladies.

06:20.262 --> 06:21.862
That'll never happen.

06:29.137 --> 06:31.038
Are we really
gonna do this?

06:31.906 --> 06:33.774
Sure we're gonna do this.

06:34.675 --> 06:37.009
How are we gonna do this?

06:39.012 --> 06:40.480
No idea.

06:42.180 --> 06:43.382
Right.

06:48.553 --> 06:50.821
Did you have a busy day?

06:50.855 --> 06:52.790
Run off my feet.
Not a minute to think.

06:55.459 --> 06:57.294
Whatever it is
I'm supposed to be

06:57.327 --> 06:59.061
doing down there, Priscilla,
I'm not doing it.

07:00.831 --> 07:02.265
Well, Daddy told me
that he thinks

07:02.298 --> 07:04.399
you're an integral part
of the company.

07:04.434 --> 07:05.935
Huh. Integral.

07:05.968 --> 07:08.135
Like the stapler on my desk.

07:08.170 --> 07:09.305
Well, it's steady,

07:09.338 --> 07:10.572
and it's what
you need right now.

07:10.607 --> 07:12.508
I know. I know.

07:15.843 --> 07:19.012
I wonder how much peppercorns
are in here.

07:19.045 --> 07:21.014
I don't know, Junior.

07:21.048 --> 07:22.548
I'd say about a thousand.

07:22.583 --> 07:25.552
No way! There got to be at
least five thousand in there.

07:25.584 --> 07:27.552
I'd put a dollar
on a thousand.

07:27.588 --> 07:30.623
Young man.

07:27.588 --> 07:30.623
Whoa, no, no, no.

07:30.656 --> 07:34.192
Young man, we do not gamble
at the dinner table.

07:34.226 --> 07:37.596
We do not gamble anyplace,
Bobby.

07:37.629 --> 07:40.665
Exactly.
We do not gamble anyplace.

07:42.533 --> 07:44.134
No, we do not.

07:48.204 --> 07:50.072
One dollar.

07:50.107 --> 07:51.107
Come on.

07:54.077 --> 07:55.110
All right.

07:55.978 --> 07:57.745
Oh, you know what?

07:57.779 --> 07:59.613
I just remembered, I need
to go back to the office

07:59.648 --> 08:01.450
and finish up some work.

08:02.283 --> 08:03.483
Now?

08:03.517 --> 08:05.718
Your father has been
so supportive, honey,

08:05.752 --> 08:07.154
that I don't want
to let him down.

08:09.122 --> 08:11.091
Delicious. Thank you.

08:11.125 --> 08:12.625
See you later, kiddo.

08:19.031 --> 08:20.632
I'm doubling down on Jack.

08:20.666 --> 08:22.633
Bobby, we got $1,200
on the table!

08:22.668 --> 08:24.736
$1,200, buddy!

08:29.807 --> 08:30.875
Bobby, you're not allowed

08:30.908 --> 08:32.609
to have dogs
that good-looking.

08:33.177 --> 08:34.177
Miss one!

08:35.379 --> 08:36.980
We got him on the run,
here we go!

08:37.014 --> 08:38.447
We got him on the run!

08:38.480 --> 08:40.015
Put the chair out there!

08:40.049 --> 08:42.751
Two chairs
and I'll raise you $500 each.

08:51.159 --> 08:52.793
Give the racket to the dog!

08:52.826 --> 08:54.861
Oh, too good for you.

09:01.134 --> 09:03.369
Jack, for the love of God!

09:03.403 --> 09:05.672
Damn it.

09:03.403 --> 09:05.672
Good game, Jack.

09:05.706 --> 09:08.274
I thought I had you
this time, I really did.

09:08.307 --> 09:10.542
That was a fine,
fine effort.

09:10.576 --> 09:11.909
Great try, great try.

09:11.945 --> 09:13.212
No, don't come over here.

09:13.245 --> 09:16.081
What do you expect, Jack?
Bobby's the world champ.

09:16.114 --> 09:19.516
No, I had an advantage.
It was three against one.

09:19.551 --> 09:22.386
It was three against one.

09:22.418 --> 09:24.386
You know what?
He keeps betting me,

09:24.422 --> 09:25.788
I don't know
what to do about it.

09:25.822 --> 09:28.524
The thing about Jack is,
he can afford to lose.

09:28.557 --> 09:30.025
You got to think
about Priscilla, Bobby.

09:30.058 --> 09:30.991
What is she gonna say?

09:31.027 --> 09:33.061
You still married, Bobby?

09:31.027 --> 09:33.061
Oh, barely.

09:33.096 --> 09:34.964
He sure will be if he shows up
in a Rolls-Royce.

09:34.998 --> 09:37.132
He sure as hell won't be if he
shows up in a Rolls-Royce.

09:37.166 --> 09:38.165
Why?

09:38.200 --> 09:39.266
Even Bobby
will find it tough

09:39.301 --> 09:40.435
to talk his way out
of that one.

09:40.469 --> 09:41.769
"Oh, honey, this crazy day!

09:41.803 --> 09:44.304
"This guy on the corner just
gave me a Silver Shadow."

09:44.337 --> 09:45.338
Think that'll cut it?

09:45.373 --> 09:46.439
Talk his way out of it?

09:46.474 --> 09:48.441
The man just won himself
a Rolls-Royce!

09:48.475 --> 09:49.542
Herb, you're not getting it.

09:49.576 --> 09:50.978
Bobby doesn't gamble anymore.

09:51.010 --> 09:52.278
Oh, he don't gamble anymore!

09:52.312 --> 09:53.312
No, no, no.

09:53.346 --> 09:54.746
Gamblers Anonymous
once a week,

09:54.780 --> 09:56.580
shrink twice a week.
I'm a reformed man.

09:56.615 --> 09:58.451
There you are.

09:56.615 --> 09:58.451
Oh, there you go.

09:58.484 --> 09:59.984
You know what? Actually,
Lornie's got a point.

10:00.019 --> 10:01.985
That vehicle's kind
of big to hide.

10:02.019 --> 10:04.588
Jack, why don't you just
keep it for a little while?

10:04.623 --> 10:06.456
You saying
I'm not good for a bet?

10:06.490 --> 10:08.725
No, no, no.
Just keep the engine warm

10:08.759 --> 10:10.159
and don't nick up the paint.

10:14.530 --> 10:15.764
"$100,000 Girl?"

10:15.798 --> 10:18.634
You don't see even a senior
tour making a hundred G's.

10:18.668 --> 10:20.202
Oh, she reckons she ought
to get more than that.

10:20.235 --> 10:21.468
Same as the men.

10:21.503 --> 10:23.738
She's not happy
with $100,000?

10:23.772 --> 10:26.141
That Billie Jean King,
what is her problem?

10:26.174 --> 10:27.841
Bobby, you got to remember,
nowadays it's all

10:27.875 --> 10:29.842
equality this, equality that.

10:29.878 --> 10:31.711
They're burning bras,
for God's sake.

10:31.746 --> 10:32.779
Why would they
ever pay the women

10:32.813 --> 10:34.113
the same as the guys?

10:34.148 --> 10:36.014
All I can tell you
is that there is nothing wrong

10:36.048 --> 10:38.616
with a nice girl in a short
skirt chasing a ball.

10:38.652 --> 10:40.753
You know,
I won the goddamn U.S. Open.

10:40.787 --> 10:43.022
I could beat Billie Jean King
or any of those women.

10:43.056 --> 10:45.323
But are they offering me
equal prize money on the tour?

10:45.356 --> 10:46.757
No, sir, I'm getting peanuts.

10:46.793 --> 10:47.993
Hey, there's a bet for you.

10:48.028 --> 10:48.927
What's that?

10:48.960 --> 10:51.028
Bobby Riggs
vs. Billie Jean King.

10:51.062 --> 10:53.264
I'd pay a lot to see that.

10:59.937 --> 11:01.171
Hey, everybody?

11:01.971 --> 11:03.773
I know
what you're all risking,

11:03.806 --> 11:06.074
because I'm risking
the exact same thing.

11:06.109 --> 11:07.009
More.

11:07.043 --> 11:10.044
No, not more.
The same.

11:10.078 --> 11:12.513
We're all putting our careers
on the line for this.

11:12.547 --> 11:14.783
So I just want to thank you
for your bravery.

11:16.018 --> 11:17.151
And your balls.

11:19.187 --> 11:21.020
Are we gonna get our hair
done before every event?

11:21.054 --> 11:22.789
Because I could
get used to this.

11:22.823 --> 11:25.791
The salon is a once-only
because the press is here.

11:25.826 --> 11:27.326
And because
I love you so much.

11:27.360 --> 11:30.028
Tomorrow the press won't be
here and I won't love you.

11:30.063 --> 11:31.663
This is a budget tour,
ladies...

11:31.697 --> 11:33.365
which means
you will be sharing rooms.

11:33.399 --> 11:34.432
So you might as well start

11:34.466 --> 11:35.633
getting to know
each other now.

11:35.667 --> 11:37.002
I call bunking with Val!

11:37.035 --> 11:39.370
I thought you were gonna
get us a sponsor, Gladys.

11:39.404 --> 11:41.273
I... was. I...

11:42.006 --> 11:43.640
...am, Rosie.

11:43.674 --> 11:47.676
It's just that right now
we are broke, so shut up.

11:47.711 --> 11:49.912
Well, wait. What about
our prize money?

11:49.947 --> 11:51.681
Oh, Val, why are you
worried about prize money?

11:51.715 --> 11:53.014
You only get that if you win.

11:54.115 --> 11:55.817
All right, you've got
30 minutes before

11:55.851 --> 11:58.385
you show your faces
to the press.

11:58.421 --> 11:59.821
Hi.

11:58.421 --> 11:59.821
Hi.

11:59.855 --> 12:01.923
I've been moving around
too much, haven't I?

12:01.956 --> 12:03.090
Yeah.

12:03.124 --> 12:06.194
I'm sorry, I've been, uh...
I'm excited.

12:07.195 --> 12:09.163
Or nervous or something.

12:09.197 --> 12:10.697
You're all tennis players?

12:10.730 --> 12:12.697
Yeah. You don't watch tennis?

12:12.732 --> 12:14.967
Oh, no. I don't have a TV.

12:15.001 --> 12:17.102
But I admire
what you guys are doing.

12:17.136 --> 12:19.103
Sounds like you girls are
getting men to pay attention

12:19.139 --> 12:21.072
to what you're saying
for once.

12:21.107 --> 12:22.707
You know what would
really get their attention?

12:22.743 --> 12:23.975
A sex strike.

12:24.009 --> 12:26.978
What? That would punish us
just as much as the men.

12:27.011 --> 12:28.812
I don't think
I'd even miss it.

12:28.846 --> 12:31.281
My ex went about it like
he was fixing the carburetor

12:31.315 --> 12:32.682
on the Oldsmobile.

12:32.716 --> 12:34.717
And he could never
get that damn car to start.

12:35.352 --> 12:36.618
Rosie, come on!

12:36.653 --> 12:38.121
At least women know
where the carburetor is.

12:40.190 --> 12:41.424
So...

12:41.457 --> 12:42.824
...Billie Jean...

12:43.594 --> 12:45.228
...what do you want?

12:48.096 --> 12:49.364
What do you mean?

12:51.634 --> 12:53.634
With your hair. What do you
want to do with it?

12:53.668 --> 12:55.870
Oh.

12:57.205 --> 12:58.372
It doesn't matter.

12:58.407 --> 12:59.973
You can just get it
out of my face.

13:00.005 --> 13:02.241
You don't care
about how you look?

13:03.376 --> 13:05.245
Someone as pretty as you?

13:07.779 --> 13:10.481
Uh, it's... I'm not...

13:10.515 --> 13:12.216
...pret... I mean, I don't...

13:13.519 --> 13:16.721
Thank you for...
for saying that.

13:20.258 --> 13:21.859
What's your name again?

13:22.658 --> 13:23.994
Marilyn.

13:29.432 --> 13:34.102
Would you let me just...
give you a little trim?

13:36.171 --> 13:40.040
It'll make you feel like
a whole new person.

13:40.075 --> 13:43.076
I don't think a haircut's ever
made me feel quite like that.

13:48.249 --> 13:49.883
Is that perfume?

13:49.917 --> 13:51.918
It's lavender oil.

13:51.951 --> 13:55.253
I put it on my wrists
just to relax the customers.

13:55.288 --> 13:56.722
It's nice.

14:37.057 --> 14:38.957
I love it.

14:38.993 --> 14:40.293
Billie Jean!

14:40.326 --> 14:42.160
Come on!

14:40.326 --> 14:42.160
I'm coming!

14:42.195 --> 14:43.061
All right!

14:43.095 --> 14:44.830
What is she doing in there?

14:44.864 --> 14:46.565
It was nice to meet you.

14:46.599 --> 14:48.167
Nice to meet you.

14:50.302 --> 14:51.969
You know what?

14:52.003 --> 14:54.272
We've got a tournament
in San Diego, actually,

14:54.306 --> 14:57.108
next month,
and I have a lot of tickets.

14:57.140 --> 14:59.074
So you could just
bring everyone and...

14:59.110 --> 15:01.110
Billie Jean, let's go!

14:59.110 --> 15:01.110
It's a lot of fun.

15:01.144 --> 15:02.846
Yeah, everyone's
invited to come.

15:02.879 --> 15:04.813
Next month in San Diego.

15:04.847 --> 15:06.414
So... thank you again.

15:06.450 --> 15:08.050
Thank you.

15:08.083 --> 15:08.950
Finally.

15:08.985 --> 15:10.118
We're gonna be late!

15:10.152 --> 15:13.221
Do you think there'll be
any cute photographers?

15:13.255 --> 15:15.322
Peaches, I know
he's very cute, but let's go.

15:15.357 --> 15:16.389
Girls, get in line.

