46:24.601 --> 46:26.334
Billie Jean has been
on me to play her,

46:26.367 --> 46:27.735
but you know what she's like.

46:27.769 --> 46:28.804
Yeah.

46:28.838 --> 46:31.506
And besides, I always say
if you're gonna play...

46:31.539 --> 46:33.641
...play the number one.

46:33.675 --> 46:35.509
Billie Jean's number one.

46:35.543 --> 46:37.978
Not if you beat her tomorrow.

46:38.012 --> 46:40.948
Isn't that right?
Is your mom gonna beat her?

46:42.615 --> 46:46.251
40 down.
"Lumberjack's tool."

46:46.286 --> 46:48.186
Four letters.

46:48.219 --> 46:49.320
Anything?

46:49.355 --> 46:50.588
Oh, my.

46:49.355 --> 46:50.588
What?

46:50.623 --> 46:52.090
It's Larry.

46:50.623 --> 46:52.090
Hmm?

46:52.492 --> 46:53.959
Larry King.

46:55.226 --> 46:56.427
Oh.

46:57.628 --> 46:58.561
Oh.

46:58.597 --> 47:00.799
I think I'd better make
a phone call.

47:13.643 --> 47:14.676
Hello?

47:14.710 --> 47:17.612
<i>Ted here, darling.
A petite heads up.</i>

47:17.646 --> 47:19.948
<i>Larry is in the building.</i>

47:19.981 --> 47:21.349
Shit.

47:19.981 --> 47:21.349
<i>Be careful.</i>

47:21.382 --> 47:22.850
Okay. Thanks.

47:24.052 --> 47:25.853
Hey.

47:24.052 --> 47:25.853
Oh.

47:26.521 --> 47:28.088
Going up?

47:26.521 --> 47:28.088
Thanks.

47:28.123 --> 47:30.423
Yeah. 31.

47:30.456 --> 47:31.657
Me, too.

47:45.003 --> 47:46.471
Starting early.

47:48.005 --> 47:49.539
Oh, well, you know
what they say...

47:49.574 --> 47:51.375
it's never too early
for champagne.

47:51.409 --> 47:53.978
My kinda girl.

47:54.010 --> 47:55.244
You here for the tennis?

47:55.278 --> 47:56.846
I sure am.

47:56.880 --> 47:57.981
Me, too.

47:58.014 --> 48:00.683
I think Billie Jean's
gonna take it.

48:01.617 --> 48:03.619
Oh, are you a fan?

48:05.086 --> 48:06.822
You could say that.

48:10.025 --> 48:11.159
After you.

48:22.302 --> 48:23.469
Well, see you around.

48:23.503 --> 48:24.769
Maybe.

48:33.311 --> 48:34.679
Hi! Oh.

48:34.713 --> 48:35.547
Hi.

48:35.579 --> 48:37.780
Hi!

48:35.579 --> 48:37.780
Hi, honey.

48:40.284 --> 48:41.751
Oh, this is Marilyn.

48:42.820 --> 48:44.086
Oh.

48:44.121 --> 48:45.722
Larry.

48:44.121 --> 48:45.722
Oh, hi, hi.

48:46.590 --> 48:47.757
Marilyn is the, the...

48:47.791 --> 48:49.191
The hairdresser around here.

48:49.224 --> 48:52.027
And... Larry is... the...

48:52.061 --> 48:53.260
The husband around here.

48:53.295 --> 48:54.628
The husband around here.

48:54.663 --> 48:57.164
Peaches wants me
to give her a blow dry.

48:57.199 --> 48:58.199
Great.

48:59.534 --> 49:00.634
Marilyn!

48:59.534 --> 49:00.634
Uh-huh?

49:00.668 --> 49:03.070
Was the ice
for Billie Jean's knees?

49:05.539 --> 49:06.839
Yeah.

49:06.873 --> 49:08.942
Yeah, I'll get that. Thanks.

49:06.873 --> 49:08.942
Bye.

49:10.010 --> 49:11.011
Bye.

49:18.418 --> 49:20.619
Here. Let me.

49:21.420 --> 49:22.619
Okay.

50:04.590 --> 50:07.192
The roads were clear,
so I made good time.

50:11.730 --> 50:13.396
I should've called ahead,

50:13.431 --> 50:15.733
letting you know
that I was coming.

50:27.208 --> 50:28.676
Leg up.

50:39.887 --> 50:40.954
Switch.

50:41.822 --> 50:43.023
Here.

50:51.063 --> 50:52.063
Uh...

51:00.637 --> 51:02.639
I'm gonna get another room.

51:07.909 --> 51:08.978
I've got phone calls to make,

51:09.012 --> 51:11.381
and you need to rest
for the finals.

52:11.833 --> 52:15.436
<i>Point to Mrs. Court. Love-15.</i>

52:31.449 --> 52:33.217
<i>Love-30.</i>

52:33.251 --> 52:35.119
Jesus Christ, Billie.

52:36.786 --> 52:39.122
Come on, dumby. Come on.

52:52.168 --> 52:55.269
<i>Love-40. Match point.</i>

53:10.751 --> 53:14.221
<i>Game, set and match
to Mrs. Court.</i>

53:38.442 --> 53:39.909
That was bad.

53:41.842 --> 53:43.911
You don't seem yourself.

53:50.251 --> 53:52.452
I was thinking of
heading home.

53:55.722 --> 53:56.990
Really?

53:58.992 --> 54:01.827
There's lots to do
from there and...

54:01.862 --> 54:03.362
...I was thinking...

54:03.394 --> 54:07.398
...I could give you some space
and let you clear your head.

54:08.367 --> 54:09.368
Mmm-hmm.

54:15.873 --> 54:18.141
Talk to you soon.

54:15.873 --> 54:18.141
Yeah.

54:24.746 --> 54:26.347
Man.

54:27.817 --> 54:29.150
Damn.

54:30.753 --> 54:31.954
Hi.

54:32.487 --> 54:33.488
Hi.

54:34.690 --> 54:36.657
Have you got a cigarette?

54:36.692 --> 54:37.891
Nope.

54:39.960 --> 54:41.794
Billie Jean know you smoke?

54:41.829 --> 54:44.798
Uh... I guess not.

54:44.831 --> 54:47.065
She's not a fan.

54:47.099 --> 54:49.367
Well, I won't tell
if you won't.

54:50.402 --> 54:54.039
Secrets, huh? There's a lot
of those going around.

54:55.974 --> 54:58.443
Marilyn, you know
how all this gets paid for?

54:59.244 --> 55:00.177
Yeah, the...

55:00.210 --> 55:04.480
...the prize money,
rackets, hotels, flights...

55:04.514 --> 55:06.382
...the food, everything?

55:06.918 --> 55:08.285
Sponsorship.

55:08.318 --> 55:10.185
And with sponsorship,
that would go away in a heartbeat

55:10.219 --> 55:13.121
if certain things
were to be made public.

55:14.523 --> 55:17.926
I only have Billie Jean's
best interests at heart.

55:18.661 --> 55:20.561
Look.

55:20.596 --> 55:21.862
You seem like
a sweet girl and...

55:21.898 --> 55:23.465
Don't condescend to me.

55:24.398 --> 55:25.766
Please.

55:25.800 --> 55:29.103
You know,
I'm not the competition.

55:29.137 --> 55:31.839
I'm just her husband,
and you're...

55:33.072 --> 55:35.141
...you're just a phase.

55:36.076 --> 55:38.378
We're both just sideshows.

55:38.411 --> 55:40.311
Tennis is her true love.

55:40.346 --> 55:44.048
And if you get between her
and the game, you'll be gone.

56:07.036 --> 56:09.336
Met Bobby Riggs last night.

56:09.371 --> 56:10.438
Funny man.

56:11.273 --> 56:12.574
Tell me you didn't.

56:12.608 --> 56:14.175
Didn't what?

56:15.710 --> 56:18.412
He just wants to play
an exhibition match is all.

56:18.445 --> 56:20.880
Now that I'm officially
number one.

56:20.914 --> 56:24.750
It's not a tennis match,
Margaret. You do know that.

56:24.784 --> 56:26.218
What do you mean?

56:26.251 --> 56:29.020
He tried that exhibition
match line on me.

56:29.054 --> 56:32.089
Oh. And I suppose
you turned him down?

56:32.123 --> 56:33.323
Are you kidding me?

56:33.358 --> 56:35.559
You think I want to join
the Bobby Riggs circus?

56:35.592 --> 56:39.163
He wants to make himself look
great and women look stupid.

56:39.197 --> 56:42.166
It's not a match.
It's a show.

56:42.199 --> 56:45.835
I can understand why you might
not want to play him, but...

56:45.869 --> 56:47.470
...I've got nothing to hide.

57:00.548 --> 57:02.849
Mind those seams
when taking that off.

57:02.884 --> 57:04.519
She's gonna play Bobby Riggs.

57:04.552 --> 57:08.855
The Arm versus The Mouth.
I know where my money's going.

57:08.889 --> 57:12.592
What if she loses, Ted?
What if she blows it?

57:12.625 --> 57:14.293
He's never gonna let it go.

57:14.327 --> 57:16.895
He's gonna make women's tennis
look like a laughingstock.

57:16.929 --> 57:19.764
Calm yourself,
Madame Superstar.

57:19.798 --> 57:21.298
Margaret is playing
better than ever,

57:21.333 --> 57:23.268
and I don't need
to remind you.

57:24.168 --> 57:26.804
<i>And strictly entre nous...</i>

57:26.838 --> 57:29.573
...we've had to make some
adjustments in the bicep area.

57:29.606 --> 57:31.039
Haven't we, Henry?

57:31.074 --> 57:33.009
About an inch and a half.

57:34.577 --> 57:35.978
I'm just glad
you're not playing him.

57:36.012 --> 57:38.047
Not a chance.

57:40.815 --> 57:42.683
Best be careful.

57:42.717 --> 57:43.985
What do you mean?

57:45.320 --> 57:48.589
The world isn't always
a forgiving place, my dear.

57:54.262 --> 57:56.597
How are you so free
with yourself?

57:57.965 --> 58:00.133
Seems like you just do
whatever you want.

58:00.166 --> 58:03.036
I don't do whatever I want.

58:03.068 --> 58:05.837
I pay taxes,
visit the dentist.

58:05.871 --> 58:07.538
You know what I mean.

58:09.074 --> 58:11.309
I'm one of eight kids.

58:11.342 --> 58:12.976
So...

58:13.010 --> 58:15.378
...no one noticed what I did.

58:15.414 --> 58:16.713
Which is probably
for the best,

58:16.746 --> 58:19.949
because I would've shocked
the hell out of all of 'em.

58:23.820 --> 58:25.221
I don't know.

58:26.389 --> 58:29.392
I live... a private life...

58:30.360 --> 58:31.527
...and...

58:31.559 --> 58:35.029
...I guess I never think that
people will care what I do.

58:41.568 --> 58:44.637
God, I think everyone
cares what I do.

58:47.039 --> 58:49.242
I'm gonna let them all down.

58:51.045 --> 58:54.380
When I was a kid,
I played at this tennis club.

58:56.514 --> 58:57.715
I was...

58:58.384 --> 58:59.650
...twelve.

59:01.585 --> 59:05.020
It was team photo time,
which is a very big deal.

59:07.057 --> 59:09.260
And my mom made me these...

59:09.293 --> 59:10.459
...white tennis shorts,

59:10.492 --> 59:12.761
because we couldn't afford
a tennis dress.

59:13.731 --> 59:15.198
And...

59:15.998 --> 59:17.365
...the man that ran it,

59:17.400 --> 59:19.134
we were all lined up
to take the photo

59:19.168 --> 59:21.103
and he pointed at me
and he said...

59:21.137 --> 59:23.672
..."That little girl
cannot be in the photo...

59:23.704 --> 59:26.239
..."because she's not
wearing a tennis dress."

59:27.141 --> 59:28.541
That must've crushed you.

59:28.577 --> 59:29.644
No.

59:31.143 --> 59:32.611
I just thought...

59:33.146 --> 59:34.748
...that does it.

59:36.882 --> 59:39.516
I'm gonna be the best.

59:39.552 --> 59:43.355
That way I can really...
change things.

59:45.090 --> 59:47.225
That way I have a voice.

59:49.894 --> 59:51.628
You have a voice.

01:00:09.945 --> 01:00:11.612
Dad?

01:00:09.945 --> 01:00:11.612
Larry!

01:00:11.646 --> 01:00:14.481
Sorry I can't stay long.
I'm training.

01:00:14.514 --> 01:00:15.915
What the hell are you wearing?

01:00:15.949 --> 01:00:17.616
Ah. It's a sauna suit.

01:00:17.650 --> 01:00:19.519
It's killing me,
but every time I breathe,

01:00:19.554 --> 01:00:20.586
I lose a pound.

01:00:20.621 --> 01:00:22.788
You hear the news?
Bobby's back!

01:00:22.822 --> 01:00:23.955
Yeah, yeah, I heard.

01:00:23.990 --> 01:00:25.324
You heard, huh?
Isn't it great?

01:00:25.358 --> 01:00:26.626
Is it really happening?

01:00:26.659 --> 01:00:29.295
Oh, it's happening.
It is happening! Say...

01:00:30.128 --> 01:00:32.096
You want to help?

01:00:30.128 --> 01:00:32.096
What with?

01:00:32.130 --> 01:00:34.998
What with?
With training, with support.

01:00:35.032 --> 01:00:37.099
Hit some balls
for your old man.

01:00:37.135 --> 01:00:38.970
Lornie's coming in.

01:00:39.003 --> 01:00:40.503
I don't know. Why me?

01:00:40.538 --> 01:00:44.007
Why you?
You're my son, that's why.

01:00:44.041 --> 01:00:46.242
Do this thing together.
Come on!

01:00:46.277 --> 01:00:48.510
The Riggs boys
against the world!

01:00:48.545 --> 01:00:50.646
You think you can beat her?

01:00:48.545 --> 01:00:50.646
Oh.

01:00:50.679 --> 01:00:53.347
This Margaret thing
is just the beginning.

01:00:53.382 --> 01:00:55.216
It's gonna be huge.

01:01:02.423 --> 01:01:04.090
<i>Three-time Wimbledon Champion,</i>

01:01:04.125 --> 01:01:06.358
<i>four times Women's
Single Champion</i>

01:01:06.393 --> 01:01:08.227
<i>in the United States...</i>

01:01:08.262 --> 01:01:10.030
<i>...winner of the Grand Slam
of tennis,</i>

01:01:10.063 --> 01:01:11.396
<i>and current leading
money winner</i>

01:01:11.431 --> 01:01:13.132
<i>of the Women's Pro Tour.</i>

01:01:13.166 --> 01:01:15.601
<i>From Australia,
meet Margaret Court.</i>

01:01:16.603 --> 01:01:17.702
<i>Her opponent...</i>

01:01:17.737 --> 01:01:19.837
<i>...twice the United States
Singles Champion,</i>

01:01:19.871 --> 01:01:21.639
<i>also a winner at Wimbledon.</i>

01:01:21.672 --> 01:01:24.107
<i>A man who in 1967
was enshrined</i>

01:01:24.141 --> 01:01:26.109
<i>into the Tennis Hall of Fame.</i>

01:01:26.143 --> 01:01:29.246
<i>Colorful and controversial
Bobby Riggs.</i>

01:01:29.280 --> 01:01:32.382
<i>Who's your money on, Jack?
Mankind or womankind?</i>

01:01:32.416 --> 01:01:34.250
Bobby Riggs,
without a doubt.

01:01:34.284 --> 01:01:36.419
Margaret Court
is a great tennis player,

01:01:36.452 --> 01:01:38.554
there's no mistake
about that, but the...

01:01:38.588 --> 01:01:41.391
<i>...thing about women
is that they find it hard</i>

01:01:41.423 --> 01:01:43.425
<i>to consistently
handle the pressure.</i>

01:01:43.458 --> 01:01:45.927
Some would say
they're not built for it.

01:01:55.902 --> 01:01:57.035
Excuse me!

01:01:57.070 --> 01:01:58.437
It's started already!

01:01:58.472 --> 01:01:59.939
Virginia Slims coming through!

01:01:59.974 --> 01:02:01.440
Where are the TVs?

01:02:01.472 --> 01:02:04.308
Quickly! Come on, Henry.

01:02:04.342 --> 01:02:06.043
We don't want to miss this.

01:02:06.079 --> 01:02:07.546
Everybody, shut up!

01:02:07.579 --> 01:02:09.514
That's the last
of our laundry quarters.

01:02:10.981 --> 01:02:12.949
It's on what channel?

01:02:12.985 --> 01:02:14.151
Can we have
some quiet here?

01:02:14.184 --> 01:02:15.652
Please?

01:02:14.184 --> 01:02:15.652
Where, on four?

01:02:15.686 --> 01:02:16.887
Yeah, it's four.

01:02:16.920 --> 01:02:17.920
Oh! There we are.

01:02:17.954 --> 01:02:19.554
Oh, my God.
This is big.

01:02:19.590 --> 01:02:21.458
Of course
it's big. It's Bobby.

01:02:21.492 --> 01:02:22.892
The one thing that man
can do is hustle.

01:02:22.927 --> 01:02:24.193
I'll say.

01:02:24.226 --> 01:02:25.927
<i>Bobby Riggs
is two games away</i>

01:02:25.961 --> 01:02:27.563
<i>from winning this first set.</i>

01:02:27.597 --> 01:02:29.030
<i>Rather easily,
I might add.</i>

01:02:29.065 --> 01:02:30.398
Oh, my God.

01:02:30.432 --> 01:02:32.300
<i>Margaret may not
realize what she's up against.</i>

01:02:32.333 --> 01:02:35.036
I think we should have been
there to support her.

01:02:35.070 --> 01:02:36.303
You have
a tournament to play.

01:02:36.338 --> 01:02:38.406
I own you, Peaches,
don't forget that.

01:02:40.240 --> 01:02:42.710
What a dreadful choice
of blue!

01:02:43.244 --> 01:02:44.478
Oh, God.

01:02:44.512 --> 01:02:46.213
<i>If she doesn't
start attacking the ball,</i>

01:02:46.246 --> 01:02:47.780
<i>she's gonna
fall into his trap.</i>

01:02:47.813 --> 01:02:49.181
She looks spooked.

01:02:49.215 --> 01:02:51.349
Do we like the dress?

01:02:51.385 --> 01:02:53.485
It's one of Ted's.
Are we allowed not to?

01:02:53.518 --> 01:02:54.985
Right behind you, darling.

01:02:55.019 --> 01:02:56.521
We love the dress!

01:02:56.556 --> 01:02:57.588
Thank you.

01:02:57.623 --> 01:02:58.655
<i>I'm just hoping that Margaret</i>

01:02:58.690 --> 01:03:00.190
<i>will really start
hitting the ball</i>

01:03:00.224 --> 01:03:02.226
<i>and follow her serve
to the net.</i>

01:03:02.260 --> 01:03:04.495
<i>I don't see how
she can win staying back.</i>

01:03:04.528 --> 01:03:06.764
<i>It looks like
Bobby's just toying with her.</i>

01:03:06.797 --> 01:03:08.364
<i>That's gonna have
a demoralizing</i>

01:03:08.398 --> 01:03:09.597
<i>effect on Margaret</i>

01:03:09.632 --> 01:03:11.099
<i>if she thinks
he's just horsing around.</i>

01:03:11.135 --> 01:03:12.635
Oh, dear.

01:03:11.135 --> 01:03:12.635
<i>Let's face it.</i>

01:03:12.668 --> 01:03:14.804
<i>She just can't handle
Bobby's game.</i>

01:03:17.407 --> 01:03:18.874
Come on!

01:03:22.010 --> 01:03:23.710
Nice one.

01:03:23.744 --> 01:03:24.846
Bravo!

01:03:26.981 --> 01:03:28.215
The Arm'll be fine.

01:03:28.250 --> 01:03:29.617
She could squeeze
the life out of that

01:03:29.650 --> 01:03:31.985
little twerp with one
tweak of her bicep.

01:03:35.255 --> 01:03:36.355
<i>40-love.</i>

01:03:36.389 --> 01:03:37.556
No, Margaret.

01:03:37.590 --> 01:03:38.990
Wake up, Margaret!

01:03:39.025 --> 01:03:40.559
I'm not liking this.

01:03:40.594 --> 01:03:42.360
Gladys, I think I'm gonna
need a cigarette.

01:03:42.394 --> 01:03:44.597
Finally,
one of my girls smokes!

01:03:45.563 --> 01:03:47.231
<i>Game to Mr. Riggs.</i>

01:03:47.266 --> 01:03:48.666
<i>Mr. Riggs leads
one set to nothing.</i>

01:03:48.699 --> 01:03:50.999
There's not a single thing

01:03:50.034 --> 01:03:51.368
I don't hate about
Bobby Riggs,

01:03:51.402 --> 01:03:53.403
not a single thing.

01:03:53.438 --> 01:03:55.805
<i>Bobby Riggs
here in the second set.</i>

01:03:55.838 --> 01:03:57.239
<i>Riggs does it again.</i>

01:03:57.273 --> 01:03:59.009
<i>Bobby's unstoppable today.</i>

01:03:59.041 --> 01:04:00.543
<i>Bobby Riggs.</i>

01:04:00.577 --> 01:04:02.544
<i>Again, Bobby Riggs.</i>

01:04:02.579 --> 01:04:04.246
<i>Margaret seems to
be off her game.</i>

01:04:04.280 --> 01:04:06.014
I'll say!

01:04:06.047 --> 01:04:07.248
<i>40-love. Beautiful.</i>

01:04:07.282 --> 01:04:08.415
This is awful.

01:04:08.449 --> 01:04:09.850
<i>Game to Mr. Riggs.</i>

01:04:09.885 --> 01:04:11.252
Really terrible.

01:04:11.286 --> 01:04:12.653
<i>Again, Bobby Riggs.</i>

01:04:12.686 --> 01:04:14.253
Let's get
another cocktail, Henry.

01:04:14.289 --> 01:04:16.257
<i>Well, as I said...</i>

01:04:16.291 --> 01:04:17.792
<i>...it's not that women
can't play tennis,</i>

01:04:17.826 --> 01:04:21.394
<i>it's just that they can't
deal with the pressure.</i>

01:04:21.429 --> 01:04:24.197
<i>Perhaps this will finally put
a stop to women players</i>

