01:19:35.114 --> 01:19:36.448
What's next?

01:19:37.350 --> 01:19:38.683
She played like an idiot.

01:19:38.719 --> 01:19:41.386
There's no comparison.
Margaret folds.

01:19:41.421 --> 01:19:43.990
You know Billie.
She loves pressure.

01:19:44.023 --> 01:19:46.391
Yeah, but her game's
off right now.

01:19:46.426 --> 01:19:48.060
It is. I mean,
I hate to say it,

01:19:48.094 --> 01:19:49.795
but my money's on Bobby.

01:19:49.828 --> 01:19:52.329
Yep. Mine, too.

01:19:52.363 --> 01:19:54.197
Money that you have
because of Billie Jean.

01:19:54.231 --> 01:19:56.167
It's not personal.
I don't want him to win.

01:19:56.201 --> 01:19:58.001
I just think he will.

01:20:10.046 --> 01:20:11.313
<i>I think that
if I had to bet money,</i>

01:20:11.345 --> 01:20:12.946
<i>I would bet on Bobby Riggs.</i>

01:20:12.980 --> 01:20:14.349
<i>Well, my money's
on Bobby Riggs.</i>

01:20:14.382 --> 01:20:16.083
<i>I've played with him.</i>

01:20:16.118 --> 01:20:17.618
<i>The man has
tremendous experience...</i>

01:20:17.652 --> 01:20:19.487
<i>...and the male muscle
is always a little</i>

01:20:19.520 --> 01:20:21.354
<i>stronger than
the female muscle.</i>

01:20:21.389 --> 01:20:23.355
<i>Billie Jean King.</i>

01:20:23.390 --> 01:20:24.891
You're gonna want to see this.

01:20:24.925 --> 01:20:26.025
What? Am I on?

01:20:26.059 --> 01:20:27.259
You got to check this out.

01:20:27.293 --> 01:20:29.694
<i>Billie Jean King
is an excellent player.</i>

01:20:29.729 --> 01:20:32.965
<i>I think that besides that,
she's a beautiful lady.</i>

01:20:32.997 --> 01:20:34.498
<i>And I like beautiful ladies.</i>

01:20:34.533 --> 01:20:36.234
<i>I saw Bobby beat Margaret,</i>

01:20:36.269 --> 01:20:38.369
<i>and I think that
he's a really tough player.</i>

01:20:38.404 --> 01:20:40.704
<i>So I'd have to give him
the edge over Billie Jean.</i>

01:20:40.738 --> 01:20:41.805
I like it.

01:20:41.838 --> 01:20:43.105
<i>The breaking
news from Forest Hills</i>

01:20:43.140 --> 01:20:44.374
<i>is that Billie Jean King...</i>

01:20:44.408 --> 01:20:45.842
<i>...has defaulted
in her third-round match</i>

01:20:45.877 --> 01:20:47.244
<i>against Julie Heldman.</i>

01:20:47.278 --> 01:20:49.079
<i>Looking tired and dispirited,</i>

01:20:49.113 --> 01:20:51.614
<i>Mrs. King left the court
after only one set.</i>

01:20:51.648 --> 01:20:53.115
<i>Speculation mounts
that pressure from</i>

01:20:53.149 --> 01:20:54.951
<i>the upcoming match
against Bobby Riggs...</i>

01:20:54.984 --> 01:20:56.517
<i>...is taking its toll.</i>

01:20:56.551 --> 01:20:59.720
Taking its toll, baby!
I knew it!

01:20:59.755 --> 01:21:02.690
She's crumbling,
and I'm hanging out by the pool!

01:21:03.891 --> 01:21:06.827
Are you scamming me
to get more practice time?

01:21:09.563 --> 01:21:10.997
I'm sick.

01:21:11.030 --> 01:21:12.631
Let me see that.

01:21:17.103 --> 01:21:18.936
Well, you're not dying.

01:21:18.970 --> 01:21:20.604
Try to sound pleased.

01:21:20.640 --> 01:21:23.608
Look, I love
the other girls, but...

01:21:23.643 --> 01:21:25.877
...you're the draw.
You're my giant.

01:21:25.909 --> 01:21:29.447
I'm a giant with the flu.
I don't know what to say.

01:21:33.117 --> 01:21:34.617
Take two weeks off!

01:21:34.652 --> 01:21:37.353
Go somewhere,
do what you need to do, okay?

01:21:37.387 --> 01:21:38.521
But you have a tournament

01:21:38.555 --> 01:21:39.822
the day after that
match with Riggs...

01:21:39.855 --> 01:21:41.657
...and, win or lose,
you're gonna be there.

01:21:42.158 --> 01:21:43.693
Okay, thank you.

01:21:43.726 --> 01:21:45.860
And just so you know,
if you lose,

01:21:45.895 --> 01:21:47.796
I will never forgive you.

01:21:54.402 --> 01:21:56.903
Oh, Jesus, Larry.

01:21:56.938 --> 01:22:00.407
It's too much. No wonder
my body's falling apart.

01:22:09.347 --> 01:22:12.250
Okay, if there's somebody
that you need...

01:22:12.283 --> 01:22:13.884
...that you want me
to call...

01:22:15.286 --> 01:22:16.753
...I can call her.

01:22:20.826 --> 01:22:22.560
No, there's nobody.

01:22:24.561 --> 01:22:26.327
<i>And if you mistake
him for a fool,</i>

01:22:26.363 --> 01:22:28.465
<i>you may end up
looking like one yourself.</i>

01:22:28.498 --> 01:22:31.132
<i>Whether he's wearing a dress,
playing with an umbrella...</i>

01:22:31.166 --> 01:22:32.333
<i>...or sporting this season's</i>

01:22:32.368 --> 01:22:35.136
<i>must-have accessory,
a flock of sheep...</i>

01:22:35.171 --> 01:22:37.005
<i>...Bobby has not
lost a match yet.</i>

01:22:37.037 --> 01:22:40.206
<i>And as the Bobby Riggs circus
moves on to the next town...</i>

01:22:40.242 --> 01:22:41.309
<i>...people are beginning
to wonder</i>

01:22:41.342 --> 01:22:43.476
<i>what has happened
to the opposition.</i>

01:22:43.511 --> 01:22:46.614
<i>Has she choked?
Has she fled the country?</i>

01:22:46.648 --> 01:22:50.417
<i>After withdrawing from
Forest Hills with a virus, nobody...</i>

01:22:50.451 --> 01:22:53.587
<i>...has seen even the ghost
of Billie Jean King.</i>

01:22:57.056 --> 01:22:59.890
Hey! Where are you going?

01:22:59.925 --> 01:23:01.525
Where is she going?

01:23:02.328 --> 01:23:03.795
My guess?

01:23:05.662 --> 01:23:06.729
Houston.

01:23:11.402 --> 01:23:12.802
She does know
what time this is...

01:23:12.836 --> 01:23:14.537
Yes, I told you.

01:23:15.271 --> 01:23:16.972
Has she pulled out?

01:23:17.006 --> 01:23:18.440
She was ill.

01:23:22.110 --> 01:23:24.045
Sorry I'm late, gentlemen.

01:23:24.079 --> 01:23:26.047
Hey, honey, how's the flu?

01:23:26.082 --> 01:23:27.782
Flu?

01:23:26.082 --> 01:23:27.782
I heard you were ill.

01:23:27.814 --> 01:23:30.583
No. Don't believe everything
you read in the papers, Bobby.

01:23:30.618 --> 01:23:33.053
But thank you for the flowers.
I gave 'em to Rosie.

01:23:33.087 --> 01:23:34.453
And I put 'em
in the trash.

01:23:34.488 --> 01:23:36.856
Oh.

01:23:36.890 --> 01:23:38.024
Billie Jean.

01:23:38.824 --> 01:23:39.826
Jack.

01:23:41.293 --> 01:23:43.729
What are you doing here?

01:23:43.761 --> 01:23:46.197
Jack's my choice
of commentator for ABC.

01:23:46.231 --> 01:23:47.432
Jack?

01:23:48.368 --> 01:23:49.801
Oh, that won't work.

01:23:49.835 --> 01:23:51.502
Now, Billie Jean,
no one's complaining

01:23:51.536 --> 01:23:53.237
about Rosie doing
the play-by-play.

01:23:53.270 --> 01:23:54.771
Well, Rosie hasn't continually

01:23:54.805 --> 01:23:56.473
tried to dismantle
women's tennis.

01:23:57.774 --> 01:24:00.277
You overstate
my influence, Billie Jean.

01:24:00.310 --> 01:24:03.345
You blackballed us
from the USLTA, Jack.

01:24:03.380 --> 01:24:05.414
We did you a favor.
Lousy organization.

01:24:05.448 --> 01:24:06.748
Jack's my choice.

01:24:06.782 --> 01:24:09.051
Sure make for
a punchy commentator.

01:24:13.722 --> 01:24:15.221
I won't play.

01:24:15.256 --> 01:24:18.391
Look, I just spent $750,000
on this event.

01:24:18.426 --> 01:24:20.494
You can't pull out
the day before the match!

01:24:21.261 --> 01:24:22.729
Says who?

01:24:23.264 --> 01:24:24.465
Say...

01:24:25.399 --> 01:24:27.433
...I wonder if we could...

01:24:27.466 --> 01:24:29.801
...have a word,
just the two of us.

01:24:42.012 --> 01:24:43.380
Billie Jean...

01:24:43.413 --> 01:24:45.148
...I know we've had
our differences,

01:24:45.182 --> 01:24:48.284
but that's behind us.

01:24:48.318 --> 01:24:50.587
This is between you
and Bobby now.

01:24:50.621 --> 01:24:51.621
Bobby?

01:24:52.355 --> 01:24:54.791
Oh, Bobby's a clown.

01:24:54.823 --> 01:24:56.724
This whole thing's
an act for him, Jack.

01:24:56.760 --> 01:24:58.458
You know that.

01:24:58.493 --> 01:25:01.529
With you it's different.
It's for real.

01:25:01.564 --> 01:25:03.030
What do you mean?

01:25:05.634 --> 01:25:07.768
I don't think
you respect women.

01:25:09.770 --> 01:25:11.871
I've been happily married
for 32 years.

01:25:11.905 --> 01:25:14.873
No, I think you like us in
the kitchen and the bedroom.

01:25:14.908 --> 01:25:17.476
I think you are a gentleman,
and I mean that.

01:25:17.510 --> 01:25:19.078
Thank you.
I'll take my compliments

01:25:19.112 --> 01:25:20.878
where I can from you.

01:25:20.913 --> 01:25:23.849
It's when we dare
to want a little bit more.

01:25:24.850 --> 01:25:27.118
Just a little bit
of what you've got.

01:25:28.052 --> 01:25:30.153
That's what you can't stand.

01:25:30.188 --> 01:25:31.355
Oh. Really?

01:25:31.389 --> 01:25:32.956
Yeah.

01:25:32.989 --> 01:25:34.623
And to have you telling
the American public

01:25:34.658 --> 01:25:36.794
what to read
into every serve?

01:25:37.328 --> 01:25:38.796
Every point?

01:25:41.265 --> 01:25:42.331
I'm sorry, Jack.

01:25:42.364 --> 01:25:44.367
If you're commentating,
I'm not playing.

01:25:44.400 --> 01:25:45.501
How do you think
that's gonna make

01:25:45.534 --> 01:25:47.501
the great Billie
Jean King look?

01:25:47.536 --> 01:25:48.636
Backing out
at the last minute

01:25:48.670 --> 01:25:51.306
just because she didn't
like the commentator?

01:25:51.340 --> 01:25:52.472
I think it's pretty
similar to how

01:25:52.507 --> 01:25:55.108
it'll make the great
Jack Kramer look.

01:25:55.141 --> 01:25:56.376
Shutting the whole thing down

01:25:56.411 --> 01:25:58.546
because he didn't
get to participate.

01:26:00.346 --> 01:26:03.114
No. That's not gonna happen.

01:26:03.149 --> 01:26:04.849
You're not gonna do this.

01:26:04.885 --> 01:26:08.253
This means too much to you.
You and your Sisterhood.

01:26:08.287 --> 01:26:09.653
You'd never throw it

01:26:09.688 --> 01:26:11.056
over something like this.
You won't.

01:26:11.090 --> 01:26:14.159
Do you remember the last time
you thought I was bluffing?

01:26:14.893 --> 01:26:16.159
One dollar.

01:26:21.565 --> 01:26:22.666
You know
the difference between

01:26:22.699 --> 01:26:24.800
a good player and a great?

01:26:24.836 --> 01:26:28.471
The great players never let
emotion get in the way.

01:26:28.506 --> 01:26:30.707
It messes with their game.

01:26:41.248 --> 01:26:42.716
Sorry, Bobby.

01:26:49.055 --> 01:26:50.623
<i>Any last
minute thoughts, Billie Jean?</i>

01:26:50.658 --> 01:26:52.225
<i>Are you going to win?</i>

01:26:52.259 --> 01:26:53.625
Of course she's gonna win.

01:26:53.659 --> 01:26:55.560
Against an old guy
like Bobby Riggs, sure.

01:26:55.595 --> 01:26:58.297
Let her play Rosewall
or Nastase.

01:26:58.329 --> 01:27:00.564
Men are better.
End of story.

01:27:00.600 --> 01:27:02.233
I'm not saying
women are better.

01:27:02.266 --> 01:27:03.568
I've never said that.

01:27:03.601 --> 01:27:06.170
I'm saying
we deserve some respect.

01:27:06.203 --> 01:27:08.704
More than Bobby Riggs
or you are giving us.

01:27:08.738 --> 01:27:10.572
Sir, do you have a daughter?

01:27:10.608 --> 01:27:13.110
Or a sister? You sure as heck
have a mother.

01:27:13.143 --> 01:27:14.676
Is your father better
than your mother?

01:27:14.711 --> 01:27:16.679
Just because he's a man?
Do you believe that?

01:27:17.081 --> 01:27:17.913
No.

01:27:17.948 --> 01:27:19.382
But that's what
you're saying...

01:27:19.416 --> 01:27:20.783
whether you think
you are or not.

01:27:20.815 --> 01:27:23.784
If I beat Bobby Riggs,
will you stop saying it?

01:27:23.819 --> 01:27:24.851
Okay.

01:27:24.886 --> 01:27:26.853
Sir, I'm gonna
hold you to that.

01:27:26.889 --> 01:27:28.856
If I see you,
I'm gonna hold you to that.

01:27:28.890 --> 01:27:30.191
Thank you.
That's it for today.

01:27:30.225 --> 01:27:31.826
We'll see you at the match.

01:28:17.332 --> 01:28:18.465
Let's get this show
on the road.

01:28:18.500 --> 01:28:19.934
Here you go, Bobby.

01:28:32.179 --> 01:28:34.746
Dad?

01:28:32.179 --> 01:28:34.746
Yeah?

01:28:34.779 --> 01:28:36.981
I'm just gonna
watch it here.

01:28:39.051 --> 01:28:42.420
What do you mean?
This is it. This is the day.

01:28:42.453 --> 01:28:44.255
I'm sorry. I'm...

01:28:45.155 --> 01:28:46.623
...I'm not coming.

01:28:49.192 --> 01:28:51.761
You don't think I'm gonna
lose, do you, kiddo?

01:28:51.795 --> 01:28:52.628
No.

01:28:52.662 --> 01:28:56.231
You'll do great.
You don't need me.

01:28:56.265 --> 01:28:57.732
Good luck, Dad.

01:29:04.872 --> 01:29:06.639
This one's from
Jennifer in Tucson.

01:29:06.675 --> 01:29:09.377
"Good luck, Billie Jean,
we're all rooting for you."

01:29:09.409 --> 01:29:10.710
This one's from Annie
from New York.

01:29:10.744 --> 01:29:12.112
"Go, Billie,
we know you're gonna win."

01:29:12.145 --> 01:29:14.646
You've lost weight.
I have to take this in.

01:29:14.681 --> 01:29:16.782
We don't have time.

01:29:14.681 --> 01:29:16.782
We have time.

01:29:16.815 --> 01:29:17.983
How you feeling, honey?

01:29:18.018 --> 01:29:19.451
Do you need anything?
Water?

01:29:19.484 --> 01:29:20.752
No, I'm good, thank you.

01:29:20.787 --> 01:29:22.186
Twenty minutes to game time.

01:29:22.220 --> 01:29:25.090
Rosie Casals,
they need you in the studio.

01:29:26.291 --> 01:29:27.759
You're gonna kill him.

01:29:28.894 --> 01:29:30.261
I'll see you guys in a bit.

01:29:30.296 --> 01:29:31.595
Good luck out there.

01:29:31.628 --> 01:29:34.198
Now, I have to ask,
do you really intend to

01:29:34.231 --> 01:29:36.332
inflict blue suede shoes...

01:29:36.367 --> 01:29:38.935
...on ninety million members
of the viewing public?

01:29:38.969 --> 01:29:41.403
How many? Oh, my God.
Billie Jean!

01:29:41.438 --> 01:29:42.505
If they're good enough
for Elvis,

01:29:42.538 --> 01:29:43.872
they're good enough for me.

01:29:43.907 --> 01:29:46.275
Well, something's off.

01:29:46.307 --> 01:29:48.609
And I think it's the shoes.

01:29:46.307 --> 01:29:48.609
It's not the shoes!

01:29:48.644 --> 01:29:50.045
Your hair?

01:29:55.984 --> 01:29:58.485
Mom, Dad, this is Marilyn.

01:29:58.520 --> 01:29:59.686
My hairdresser.

01:29:59.720 --> 01:30:02.688
Pleased to meet you.

01:30:02.721 --> 01:30:04.823
Well, if there's one thing
I know, it's...

01:30:04.859 --> 01:30:07.794
...never get between a woman
and her hairdresser.

01:30:07.827 --> 01:30:09.494
Very funny. Yes indeed.

01:30:09.528 --> 01:30:11.363
Come on.
Let's find our seats.

01:30:11.396 --> 01:30:13.332
Here. I'll take you up there.

01:30:17.668 --> 01:30:18.869
Good luck.

01:30:19.270 --> 01:30:20.369
Thank you.

01:30:20.404 --> 01:30:21.871
Yeah, give 'em heck.

01:30:21.904 --> 01:30:24.373
Billie Jean, I'll be back
to take you to the court.

01:30:24.408 --> 01:30:25.409
All right.

01:30:28.345 --> 01:30:30.213
Hi.

01:30:28.345 --> 01:30:30.213
Hi.

01:30:33.882 --> 01:30:35.885
Your hairdresser, huh?

01:30:38.287 --> 01:30:39.587
What was I supposed to say?

01:30:39.621 --> 01:30:41.021
No, you're right.

01:30:42.158 --> 01:30:43.758
That's why I'm here.

01:30:47.094 --> 01:30:48.862
Come on.

01:30:48.895 --> 01:30:52.532
Yeah, just like that.
That looks great.

01:30:52.564 --> 01:30:55.268
Yep, zip her up. Oh, boy!

01:30:55.301 --> 01:30:57.435
We need the "Sugar Daddy"
facing camera.

01:30:57.470 --> 01:30:59.337
Mmm-hmm.

01:30:57.470 --> 01:30:59.337
We got to see that.

01:30:59.371 --> 01:31:01.472
Do you want me to hold it
from the stick?

01:31:01.506 --> 01:31:03.407
Uh...

01:31:01.506 --> 01:31:03.407
Am I gonna hold it that way?

01:31:03.442 --> 01:31:05.141
That looks great.

01:31:05.176 --> 01:31:07.877
We're trying to prepare
for the match.

01:31:07.912 --> 01:31:09.713
So the camera can see it.

01:31:09.747 --> 01:31:11.681
Yeah, up high.
Beautiful.

01:31:11.716 --> 01:31:14.018
I'll get it up
nice and high.

01:31:14.051 --> 01:31:16.085
We got it. Thank you.

01:31:14.051 --> 01:31:16.085
Have a great match.

01:31:16.119 --> 01:31:18.988
Thank you. Thank you,
ladies. See you out there.

01:31:19.988 --> 01:31:23.023
See you out there.
Good work.

01:31:23.057 --> 01:31:24.926
Do it for the men, Bobby.

01:31:25.395 --> 01:31:26.728
Wow. You good?

01:31:26.761 --> 01:31:28.229
Yeah! I'm ready for battle.

01:31:28.262 --> 01:31:31.431
Stand by, Howard.
We are live in five...

01:31:31.466 --> 01:31:34.068
...four...three...

01:31:36.938 --> 01:31:40.306
<i>The following
is an exclusive presentation</i>

01:31:40.341 --> 01:31:41.441
<i>of ABC Sports.</i>

01:31:41.475 --> 01:31:44.910
<i>Live from the Astrodome
in Houston, Texas...</i>

01:31:44.944 --> 01:31:47.179
<i>...the Tennis Battle
of the Sexes,</i>

01:31:47.212 --> 01:31:50.782
<i>Billie Jean King
vs. Bobby Riggs.</i>

01:31:50.815 --> 01:31:52.315
<i>What a scene it is!</i>

01:31:52.350 --> 01:31:53.716
<i>The Houston Astrodome...</i>

01:31:53.752 --> 01:31:55.386
<i>...where up till now
they've played</i>

01:31:55.420 --> 01:31:59.123
<i>almost every sport
in the world except tennis.</i>

01:31:59.157 --> 01:32:02.259
<i>But in this panoramic scene,
a happening.</i>

01:32:02.292 --> 01:32:03.826
<i>With the big band here,</i>

01:32:03.859 --> 01:32:07.128
<i>with dancing cheerleaders,
and all of the rest.</i>

01:32:07.162 --> 01:32:09.163
<i>It's hard to believe,
but probably</i>

01:32:09.198 --> 01:32:12.434
<i>more than 30,000 people
are in this arena...</i>

01:32:12.467 --> 01:32:14.635
<i>...for an all-time-record
tennis audience</i>

01:32:14.670 --> 01:32:16.369
<i>anywhere in the world.</i>

01:32:29.048 --> 01:32:31.417
And zoom in on five.

01:32:31.451 --> 01:32:32.819
Is that a priest?

01:32:32.851 --> 01:32:35.153
